commit.message:
Clearly document supported operating systems

See issue 4 on GitHub:
  https://github.com/xolox/python-capturer/issues/4
Fix broken (previously unused) method proxy support

Refactor makefile, setup script, Travis CI support and more

I more or less touched everything except the Python code, in
the process adding code style checks (also on Travis CI),
wheel distribution support, Mac OS X testing on Travis CI,
improvements to the online documentation (specifically with
regards to the proxy methods), plus lots of minor details.
Fix some (but not yet all) PEP-257 violations.
Make it easier to run test suite from PyPI release (fixes #3)

Make "nested" output capturing work as expected (issue #2)

Refer to issue 2 on GitHub for details:
  https://github.com/xolox/python-capturer/issues/2
